title: 2 teenagers ID'd as victims in Huntsville double homicide
content:
Two teenagers were the victims of a Tuesday morning double homicide in Huntsville, authorities said.
Madison County Deputy Coroner Tyler Berryhill said Jaylen Cosby, 19, and Khayree Austin, 17, were found dead of gunshot wounds in a house located in the 3900 block of Broadmor Drive at around 7:30 a.m.
Cosby lived at the residence, he said.
Investigators are still trying to determine the motive behind the slayings, Lt. Stacy Bates said.
Anyone with information on the shootings is asked to call the Huntsville Police Department at 256-722-7100.
